cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.SY

The paper discusses two-player zero-sum games on graphs, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The use of randomized strategies and transitions is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves analyzing the complexity of these games, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the interaction between players, which can be modeled as a system (cs.SY).
